    Files/Aplications
whereis = find all locations of an application

    System control
pidof = find pid of a given running application
pgrep = find pid of a given running application if you only know part of the name

    Networking
netstat -na | grep "PORT" see what is using a certain port
ss = check open ports and see what they do 

    Information
whatis = ask shell what a certain app/command is



